doc.previous: In April 2012, Eurocopter announced that the 500th EC145 had been delivered.[20] On 31 July 2014, the first EC145 T2, an updated variant, was delivered to its launch customer, DLR Luftrettung, who have ordered a total of 20 such helicopters for emergency medical service operations.[9] In April 2015, Airbus Group Australia Pacific delivered its first H145, previously designated as the EC145 T2.[30]
doc.after: As of September 2012, the EC145 is in service with a total of 100 customers in 34 countries.[33]
